HEADWORD: Sapwood
<hw>Sap"wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The alburnum, or part of the wood of any exogenous tree next to the
bark, being that portion of the tree through which the sap flows most
freely; -- distinguished from <contr>heartwood</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sarabaite</ent>⟦br⟧
